Shadow mapping demo. It is using a 4-samples PCF to smooth the final shadow.

q or ESC to exit
The arrow keys rotate the light
The ASWD keys zooms in or out and sidestep
The mouse+button 1 rotate the perspective
The mouse+button 2 rotate the scene
The mouse scroll-wheel zooms in or out

0 - increase dr. freak animation
9 - decrease dr. freak animation
p - toggle ogros running
h - kill dr. freak!
r - toggle wireframe
f - toggle fps on/off
g - switch bump-mapping and shadowing on/off
o/i - increase/decrease polygon offset (scale factor)
l/k - increase/decrease polygon offset (bias factor)

The following switches on the command line are available:

 --full or -s         : display full screen
 --fps[=t]  or -f[t]  : average frames per second every t seconds (default 5)
                        and displays both to stdout and, if possible, to screen.
 --info  or -i        : display X11/OpenGL and program info
 --fsaa  or -m        : enable anti-aliasing
 --aniso[=l] or-a[l]  : enable xl anisotropic filtering (default 16)
 --runlength=L or -rL : run the demo for L secs, then exit
 --version or -v      : display version and exit
 --help or -h         : display help information

The application can terminate gracefully on receiving a SIGINT, SIGTERM or
SIGHUP signal.
Averaged fps are displayed at program termination.